Foot and mouth disease, Israel
------------------------------
Information received on 17 May 2011 from Dr Michel Bellaiche,
Director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Development, Beit Dagan, Israel

Summary
-------
Report type: Follow-up report No. 2
Start date: 17 Apr 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 27 Apr 2011
Report date: 17 May 2011
Date submitted to OIE: 17 May 2011
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 27 Mar 2011
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic),
Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country


New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (Tuba-Zangariyye): Tuba-Zangariyye, Tsefat, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak 06 May 2011
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 702/ 70/ 0/ 0/ 0
Sheep/ 100/ 30/ 0/ 0/ 0

Affected Population: 4 locations in the same village:
1. The herd contains 60 cows, about 40 calves and 2 bulls. 30 of them
were affected, including the bulls.
2. The herd contains 600 fattening calves. 40 of them were affected.
3. The herd contains 40 sheep. 10 of them were affected.
4. The herd contains 60 sheep. 20 of them were affected.

Outbreak 2 (Kefar Szold): Kefar Szold, Tsefat, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 17 May 2011
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 800/ 19/ 0/ 0/ 0

Affected Population: 4 herds of 200 each - free-ranging beef cattle.
2 of the herds were affected. In one herd, 6 animals show clinical
signs and, in the second herd, 13 animals show clinical signs. On 17
May 2011 - Suspicion only: the laboratory results are pending.

Outbreak 3 (Sharona): Sharona, Kineret, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 May 2011
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 1060/ 21/ 0/ 0/ 0
Sheep/ 1500/ 37/ 22/ 0/ 0

Affected Population: 3 herds in Sharona were affected:
1. 900 ewes and goats and 600 youngs with a mortality of 22 youngs
(10 days old). In post-mortem, a "tiger heart" has been observed. 2.
1000 fattening calves 7-10 months old. 15 of them were affected.
3. 60 fattening calves 4-5 months old. 6 of them were affected.

Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 2562/ 110/ 0/ 0/ 0
Sheep/ 1600/ 67/ 22/ 0/ 0

Outbreak statistics:
1. Species: cattle
Apparent morbidity rate: 4.29 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 0.00 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 0.00 percent
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: 0.00 percent

2. Species: Sheep
Apparent morbidity rate: 4.19 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 1.38 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 32.84
Proportion susceptible animals lost*: 1.38 percent

* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or
inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: The affected herds were vaccinated last
year.

Control measures
Measures applied: Quarantine, Movement control inside the country,
Zoning, Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
No treatment of affected animals.

Measures to be applied: Screening, Disinfection of infected
premises/establishment(s)

